    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Trim the green stalk[s] off your<strong> aubergine[s] </strong>and discard, then chop into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Combine <strong>half </strong>your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>paprika</strong> (save the rest for later!) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> in a small bowl and set aside to infuse – this is your <strong>paprika oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1716278681328-x200.jpg",
